  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of life-saving health intervention to affected population in Benue State</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to provide access to life-saving primary health care services and a robust early warning disease surveillance system to the displaced population in Benue State, North-Central Nigeria. This will be achieved through strengthening existing health system surveiilance capacity. Where IDPs are located in areas where there is no immediate existing health facilities, mobile teams will be deployed. The SMOH and communities will be engaged for coordination and monitoring purposes.</narrative>
  </description>
